<FONT SIZE="2" face="arial,helvetica">
<h4>
	Minutes from ACE-grid meeting on the AccessGrid

</h4></FONT>
<i>	May 31, 2002</i>
<ul>
<pre> 
Here are brief notes from the meeting and draft agenda for GGF5:

* We are noticing a lot of cross over between individual scenario
  drafts. Recommend creating a final document with a merged set of
  requirements plus appended individual scenarios to see nuances
  particular to the application area.

* Try and get individual scenario drafts out over the weekend.

* Try and get a merged document by Mid June

* Mike will ask Julie when submission deadlines are for GGF documents.

* Invite Mary Thompson and Von Welch to look over the merged document.

* Begin working on integration of real security implementations for each
  of the respective areas (Teleimmersion, Access Grid, Dynamic and Asych
  Environments, Remote Visualization) to serve as reality check for the
  security document- to identifiy the minimum set of requirements rather
  than the idealized set.

* Deb Agarwal and Brian Corrie will not be attending GGF5. Mary Thompson
  will cover.

* Agenda for GGF5

  Session 1
  = Review merged security requirements document

  Session 2
  = Discuss other areas relevant to ACE:
	- File transfer (invite Bill(?) Allcock)
	- Web services: Marcus (lastname?)
  = Fusion community- General Atomics to talk about their requirements for
    collaborative environments.


</pre>        
</ul>




